The paper deals with algorithms for computing approximate hulls and centerpoints for collections of matrices in positive definite space, which involves concepts from computational geometry (cs.CG) and data structures (cs.DS). The applications mentioned in the abstract also suggest a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the use of horoballs as a key concept suggests a possible connection to computational topology (cs.SI).
